  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Motivated by the wide applications of BTZ black holes and interesting results of gravity's rainbow, we consider a three dimensional rainbow solutions and investigate their thermodynamic properties. We take into account the various models of linear and nonlinear electrodynamics and study their effects on the gravity's rainbow spacetime. We also examine thermal stability and find that obtained three dimensional rainbow black holes are thermally stable.</subfield>
